commands
--------------
1)cat /etc/hosts | grep -i ----> To Read 
2)ssh -1 'ford\$srashee5' cluster name ---> To login to the cluster
3)node show ---> To check no of nodes
4)version  ----> To check the version of nodes
5)sysconfig -v :---->To see the system configuration in details
6)aggr show --->To see the aggregates present in cluster 
7)rows 0 ---> To get a proper view
8)aggr show -fields node --->To show the aggregate with field node
9)aggr show -fields node,root --->To show the aggregate with field root
10)node run -node <node name> ---> To get inside the node (Eg: node run -node "test"(nodename/number)
11)vserver show -vserver "test" ---> To see the particular 
12)cifs share show -vserver "test" ---> To see share in the volume
13)vol show -vserver isg9010201 ---> To get the size of the volume
14)fields ---> To see the particular 
15)Run ---> cmd ---> nslookup --->To find out ip address
16)Run ---> cmd ---> mstsc ---> To open windows server
17)snapshot show -vserver "test" -volume "test_proj" -fields create-time xxxx ---> To see the create time of that snapsnots in that volume
18)snapshot show -vserver "test" -volume "test"j ---> To get the snapshots 
19)quota policy rule ---> To see quota policy
20)quota policy rule modify -vserver test -policy-name default -volume test_proj -type tree -target 01_Common_Folder -qtree "" -disk-limit 19GB ---> To add a extra limit to the qtree
21)node show -fields serialnumber ----> To see serial number
